(
<bibRefCitation id="EFF74B0FFFE6FF8EFBF0F908FB662485" author="Silen" box="[1138,1275,1730,1755]" pageId="4" pageNumber="475" refString="Silen, L. (1941) Cheilostomata Anasca (Bryozoa) collected by Prof. Dr. Sixten Bock's expedition to Japan and the Bonin Islands 1914. Arkiv for Zoologi, 33 A (12), 1 - 130, 9 pls." type="journal article" year="1941">Silén, 1941</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, reported by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFF74B0FFFE6FF8EFF15F92CFE6D24A1" author="Mawatari" box="[151,496,1766,1791]" pageId="4" pageNumber="475" refString="Mawatari, S. &amp; Mawatari, S. F. (1980) Studies on Japanese anascan Bryozoa 5. Division Malacostege [sic] (3). Bulletin of the Liberal Arts and Science Course, School of Medicine of Nihon University, 8, 21 - 114." type="journal article" year="1980">Mawatari &amp; Mawatari (1980)</bibRefCitation>
from Atami in 
<collectingRegion id="49A2F81CFFE6FF8EFD32F92CFC0524A1" box="[688,920,1766,1791]" country="Japan" name="Shizuoka" pageId="4" pageNumber="475">Shizuoka prefecture</collectingRegion>
, Honshu, was originally described from the 
<location id="8EB96025FFE6FF8EFF15F8C0FE3A257D" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03CF87E8FFE6FF8FFF15FD3DFC862512:8EB96025FFE6FF8EFF15F8C0FE3A257D" box="[151,423,1802,1827]" country="Cuba" name="Ryukyu (Bonin) Islands" pageId="4" pageNumber="475" stateProvince="Shizuoka prefecture">Ryukyu (Bonin) Islands</location>
.
</materialsCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD936FEFFE6FF8EFF45F8E4FA012588" blockId="4.[151,1437,866,2007]" pageId="4" pageNumber="475">
<taxonomicName id="4C664D7DFFE6FF8EFF45F8E4FE062518" box="[199,411,1838,1862]" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Calloporidae" genus="Retevirgula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="4" pageNumber="475" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="species" species="asiana" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis id="B912EAECFFE6FF8EFF45F8E4FE062518" box="[199,411,1838,1862]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="475">Retevirgula asiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B912EAECFFE6FF8EFE26F8E4FE782519" bold="true" box="[420,485,1838,1863]" pageId="4" pageNumber="475">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2215797FFE6FF8EFE26F8E4FE782519" box="[420,485,1838,1863]" pageId="4" pageNumber="475" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
differs from the fossil found in 
<collectingRegion id="49A2F81CFFE6FF8EFCD5F8E4FC542519" box="[855,969,1838,1863]" country="United States of America" name="California" pageId="4" pageNumber="475">California</collectingRegion>
and living 
<taxonomicName id="4C664D7DFFE6FF8EFBCFF8E5FB512518" box="[1101,1228,1838,1862]" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Calloporidae" genus="Retevirgula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="4" pageNumber="475" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="species" species="areolata">
<emphasis id="B912EAECFFE6FF8EFBCFF8E5FB512518" box="[1101,1228,1838,1862]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="475">R. areolata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having slightly fewer spines, a proportionally smaller avicularium, not found distal to an autozooid, more numerous kenozooids and larger interzooidal spaces. 
<taxonomicName id="4C664D7DFFE6FF8EFE70F8BCFD6925D0" box="[498,756,1910,1934]" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Calloporidae" genus="Retevirgula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="4" pageNumber="475" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="species" species="periporosa">
<emphasis id="B912EAECFFE6FF8EFE70F8BCFD6925D0" box="[498,756,1910,1934]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="475">Retevirgula periporosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry id="F371766EFFE6FF8EFCBBF8BCFCE925D1" box="[825,884,1910,1935]" name="Cuba" pageId="4" pageNumber="475">Cuba</collectingCountry>
has more spines (16–18) than 
<taxonomicName id="4C664D7DFFE6FF8EFB4EF8BDFAAB25D0" box="[1228,1334,1911,1934]" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Calloporidae" genus="Retevirgula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="4" pageNumber="475" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="species" species="asiana">
<emphasis id="B912EAECFFE6FF8EFB4EF8BDFAAB25D0" box="[1228,1334,1911,1934]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="475">R. asiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(12–14), but other characters appear similar. Based on Silén’s (1941) illustrations and description, 
<taxonomicName id="4C664D7DFFE6FF8EFB30F851FACE25ED" box="[1202,1363,1947,1971]" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Calloporidae" genus="Retevirgula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="4" pageNumber="475" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="species" species="triangulata">
<emphasis id="B912EAECFFE6FF8EFB30F851FACE25ED" box="[1202,1363,1947,1971]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="475">R. triangulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a proportionally larger avicularium with a circular rostral/opesial area. Of the mainland records for 
<collectingCountry id="F371766EFFE6FF8EFAB2F875FAEE2588" box="[1328,1395,1983,2006]" name="Japan" pageId="4" pageNumber="475">Japan</collectingCountry>
, 
<emphasis id="B912EAECFFE6FF8EFA06F875FA012588" box="[1412,1436,1983,2006]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="475">R.</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD936FEFFE7FF8FFF15FF52FDE32343" blockId="5.[151,1436,151,285]" pageId="5" pageNumber="476">
<taxonomicName id="4C664D7DFFE7FF8FFF15FF52FE8C22F1" box="[151,273,152,175]" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Calloporidae" genus="Retevirgula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="5" pageNumber="476" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="species" species="periporosa">
<emphasis id="B912EAECFFE7FF8FFF15FF52FE8C22F1" box="[151,273,152,175]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="476">periporosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C664D7DFFE7FF8FFECBFF53FE7A22EE" box="[329,487,152,176]" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Calloporidae" genus="Retevirgula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="5" pageNumber="476" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="species" species="triangulata">
<emphasis id="B912EAECFFE7FF8FFECBFF53FE7A22EE" box="[329,487,152,176]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="476">R. triangulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, both 
<emphasis id="B912EAECFFE7FF8FFDB2FF53FDF322EE" box="[560,622,153,176]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="476">sensu</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFF74B0FFFE7FF8FFDF4FF5DFC5522EE" author="Mawatari" box="[630,968,151,176]" pageId="5" pageNumber="476" refString="Mawatari, S. &amp; Mawatari, S. F. (1980) Studies on Japanese anascan Bryozoa 5. Division Malacostege [sic] (3). Bulletin of the Liberal Arts and Science Course, School of Medicine of Nihon University, 8, 21 - 114." type="journal article" year="1980">Mawatari &amp; Mawatari (1980)</bibRefCitation>
, have similar spine numbers to 
<taxonomicName id="4C664D7DFFE7FF8FFAB3FF53FA0122F1" box="[1329,1436,152,176]" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Calloporidae" genus="Retevirgula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="5" pageNumber="476" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="species" species="asiana">
<emphasis id="B912EAECFFE7FF8FFAB3FF53FA0122F1" box="[1329,1436,152,176]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="476">R. asiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and either could be conspecific. Curiously, neither 
<bibRefCitation id="EFF74B0FFFE7FF8FFD70FF76FBD0228A" author="Mawatari" box="[754,1101,188,213]" pageId="5" pageNumber="476" refString="Mawatari, S. &amp; Mawatari, S. F. (1980) Studies on Japanese anascan Bryozoa 5. Division Malacostege [sic] (3). Bulletin of the Liberal Arts and Science Course, School of Medicine of Nihon University, 8, 21 - 114." type="journal article" year="1980">Mawatari &amp; Mawatari (1980)</bibRefCitation>
nor 
<bibRefCitation id="EFF74B0FFFE7FF8FFB08FF76FA87228A" author="Silen" box="[1162,1306,188,213]" pageId="5" pageNumber="476" refString="Silen, L. (1941) Cheilostomata Anasca (Bryozoa) collected by Prof. Dr. Sixten Bock's expedition to Japan and the Bonin Islands 1914. Arkiv for Zoologi, 33 A (12), 1 - 130, 9 pls." type="journal article" year="1941">Silén (1941)</bibRefCitation>
mentioned interzooidal kenozooids in any of the material they described, though they must presumably have been present; perhaps some were mistaken for avicularia.
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF196676FFE7FF8FFF15FAC7FDC02721" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/265085/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="476" targetBox="[260,1328,338,1271]" targetPageId="5">
<paragraph id="8BD936FEFFE7FF8FFF15FAC7FDC02721" blockId="5.[151,1436,1293,1407]" pageId="5" pageNumber="476">
<emphasis id="B912EAECFFE7FF8FFF15FAC7FEA2277D" bold="true" box="[151,319,1293,1315]" pageId="5" pageNumber="476">FIGURES 4–7.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C664D7DFFE7FF8FFEC8FAC7FD93277A" box="[330,526,1293,1316]" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Calloporidae" genus="Retevirgula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="5" pageNumber="476" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="species" species="asiana" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis id="B912EAECFFE7FF8FFEC8FAC7FD93277A" box="[330,526,1293,1316]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="476">Retevirgula asiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B912EAECFFE7FF8FFD9AFAC7FDCB277D" bold="true" box="[536,598,1293,1315]" pageId="5" pageNumber="476">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2215797FFE7FF8FFD9AFAC7FDCB277D" box="[536,598,1293,1315]" pageId="5" pageNumber="476" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, Stn I3 near Cheongsan Island. 
<emphasis id="B912EAECFFE7FF8FFC36FAC7FC5A277D" bold="true" box="[948,967,1293,1315]" pageId="5" pageNumber="476">4,</emphasis>
Unbleached zooids with periopesial spines; scalebar 400 µm. 
<emphasis id="B912EAECFFE7FF8FFECCFAE6FEFC271C" bold="true" box="[334,353,1324,1346]" pageId="5" pageNumber="476">5,</emphasis>
Part of a colony with numerous kenozooids and an interzooidal avicularium (arrow); scalebar 200 µm. 
<emphasis id="B912EAECFFE7FF8FFA0BFAE6FA06271C" bold="true" box="[1417,1435,1324,1346]" pageId="5" pageNumber="476">6,</emphasis>
Part of a colony showing kenozooids with spine bases and a retained entire spine (arrows); scalebar 400 µm. 
<emphasis id="B912EAECFFE7FF8FFB65FA81FB64273F" bold="true" box="[1255,1273,1355,1377]" pageId="5" pageNumber="476">7,</emphasis>
Close-up of the avicularium shown in fig. 5; scalebar 50 µm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BD936FEFFE7FF8FFF45FA62FDAA24C9" blockId="5.[151,1437,1446,1868]" pageId="5" pageNumber="476">
In general appearance, 
<taxonomicName id="4C664D7DFFE7FF8FFE5CFA62FDD227E1" box="[478,591,1448,1471]" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Calloporidae" genus="Retevirgula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="5" pageNumber="476" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="species" species="asiana" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis id="B912EAECFFE7FF8FFE5CFA62FDD227E1" box="[478,591,1448,1471]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="476">R. asiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B912EAECFFE7FF8FFDDEFA6CFD3F27E1" bold="true" box="[604,674,1446,1471]" pageId="5" pageNumber="476">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2215797FFE7FF8FFDDEFA6CFD3F27E1" box="[604,674,1446,1471]" pageId="5" pageNumber="476" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
appears closest to 
<taxonomicName id="4C664D7DFFE7FF8FFC12FA6DFECE27BD" authority="Chimenz, Nicoletti &amp; Boncambi, 1997" authorityName="Chimenz, Nicoletti &amp; Boncambi" authorityYear="1997" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Calloporidae" genus="Retevirgula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="5" pageNumber="476" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="species" species="akdenizae">
<emphasis id="B912EAECFFE7FF8FFC12FA6DFB1227E1" box="[912,1167,1447,1471]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="476">Retevirgula akdenizae</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFF74B0FFFE7FF8FFB1FFA6CFECE27BD" author="Chimenz" pageId="5" pageNumber="476" refString="Chimenz, C., Nicoletti, L. &amp; Lippi Boncambi, F. (1997) First record of the genus Retevirgula in the Mediterranean Sea, with description of R. akdenizae sp. n. (Bryozoa, Cheilostomata). Italian Journal of Zoology, 64, 279 - 282. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 11250009709356209" type="journal article" year="1997">Chimenz, Nicoletti &amp; Boncambi, 1997</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, from the Aegean Sea area of 
<collectingCountry id="F371766EFFE7FF8FFD25FA01FD6527BA" box="[679,760,1483,1508]" name="Turkey" pageId="5" pageNumber="476">Turkey</collectingCountry>
, which has a similar-shaped avicularium. This species is the only known 
<taxonomicName id="4C664D7DFFE7FF8FFEAEFA25FE332459" box="[300,430,1519,1543]" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Calloporidae" genus="Retevirgula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="5" pageNumber="476" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B912EAECFFE7FF8FFEAEFA25FE332459" box="[300,430,1519,1543]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="476">Retevirgula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the vast area of Europe, Africa and the Indian Ocean and may possibly be an immigrant to the Mediterranean. In spite of its similarity to 
<taxonomicName id="4C664D7DFFE7FF8FFCD7F9DEFC5F2475" box="[853,962,1556,1579]" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Calloporidae" genus="Retevirgula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="5" pageNumber="476" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="species" species="asiana">
<emphasis id="B912EAECFFE7FF8FFCD7F9DEFC5F2475" box="[853,962,1556,1579]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="476">R. asiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, it differs in having larger zooids (mean length 470 µm, mean width 260 µm) with granules on the thin cryptocystal rim; additionally, it has 13–16 periopesial spines that are longer (300–400 µm) than in 
<taxonomicName id="4C664D7DFFE7FF8FFC92F996FCE7242D" box="[784,890,1628,1651]" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Calloporidae" genus="Retevirgula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="5" pageNumber="476" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="species" species="asiana">
<emphasis id="B912EAECFFE7FF8FFC92F996FCE7242D" box="[784,890,1628,1651]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="476">R. asiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Avicularia are larger and may bear a spine, and the kenozooids have up to six spines.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C37C6575FFE7FF8FFF45F969FBFC2579" pageId="5" pageNumber="476" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BD936FEFFE7FF8FFF45F969FBFC2579" blockId="5.[151,1437,1446,1868]" pageId="5" pageNumber="476">
The attribution of 
<taxonomicName id="4C664D7DFFE7FF8FFE10F969FD8924E5" box="[402,532,1699,1723]" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Calloporidae" genus="Retevirgula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="5" pageNumber="476" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B912EAECFFE7FF8FFE10F969FD8924E5" box="[402,532,1699,1723]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="476">Retevirgula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to the resurrected family-rank taxon Ellisinidae (
<bibRefCitation id="EFF74B0FFFE7FF8FFBBAF969FB7924E5" author="Vigneaux" box="[1080,1252,1699,1724]" pageId="5" pageNumber="476" refString="Vigneaux, M. (1949) Revision des Bryozoaires neogenes du Bassin d'Aquitaine et essai de classification. Memoires de la Societe Geologique de France, n. ser. 28, 1 - 153, 11 pls." type="book chapter" year="1949">Vigneaux 1949</bibRefCitation>
) is explained by Gordon (in press). 
<emphasis id="B912EAECFFE7FF8FFEF1F902FE7D2481" box="[371,480,1735,1759]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="476">Inter alia</emphasis>
, the ooecium in ellisinid genera is always associated with a heterozooid, either an avicularium or a kenozooid, both ooecial layers are calcified (some species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C664D7DFFE7FF8FFB8DF921FB0C255D" box="[1039,1169,1771,1795]" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Calloporidae" genus="Retevirgula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="5" pageNumber="476" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B912EAECFFE7FF8FFB8DF921FB0C255D" box="[1039,1169,1771,1795]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="476">Retevirgula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have, however, a small ectooecial foramen), and the zooidal cryptocyst is minimally developed, with no shelf.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C37C6575FFE7FF8FFF45F8F9FC862512" box="[199,795,1843,1868]" pageId="5" pageNumber="476" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BD936FEFFE7FF8FFF45F8F9FC862512" blockId="5.[151,1437,1446,1868]" box="[199,795,1843,1868]" pageId="5" pageNumber="476">
<emphasis id="B912EAECFFE7FF8FFF45F8F9FEFD2512" bold="true" box="[199,352,1843,1868]" pageId="5" pageNumber="476">Distribution.</emphasis>
<collectingCountry id="F371766EFFE7FF8FFEE5F8FEFE2D2515" box="[359,432,1844,1867]" name="South Korea" pageId="5" pageNumber="476">Korea</collectingCountry>
: South Sea; 
<quantity id="4C9E9B1BFFE7FF8FFDB8F8F9FDEE2515" box="[570,627,1843,1867]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.2" pageId="5" pageNumber="476" unit="m" value="42.0">42 m</quantity>
depth on rock.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
